    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by **Kyle Tucker**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 76.70. With a favorable matchup against the right-handed Lorenzen and significant park-factor support, **Kyle Tucker** is in a prime spot to contribute across all five categories. Following closely, **Miguel Vargas** (66.77) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.97) provide exceptional value. **Miguel Vargas** benefits from a 10% park boost and favorable delivery metrics from the opposing pitcher that inflate his stolen base probability, while **Jacob Wilson** leverages a leadoff spot and a significant park factor boost to maximize his production profile. **Marcell Ozuna** also cracks our top tier (63.70) despite facing the formidable McClanahan; the combination of a high-ceiling matchup and favorable wind conditions out of the park gives him a substantial edge over his raw baseline.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Heliot Ramos**, who sat at a 52.42 score, just narrowly missing the cut behind **Josh Lowe**. While **Heliot Ramos** offers solid potential, he was squeezed out by the efficiency of our OF/UTIL depth, specifically the high-ceiling platoon advantages presented to **Andy Pages** and **Luis Robert Jr.** against their respective right-handed opponents. While **Luis Robert Jr.** struggles with platoon splits, his elite skill-to-matchup conversion rate against the opposing pitcher today offsets those concerns. We are closely monitoring the risk profile of **Jackson Merrill**; despite a solid score of 54.06, he faces a very tough outing against Urena, whose 2.35 xERA represents the most significant hurdle in our starting nine. Managers should be prepared for lower-than-projected output from the bottom of the order if Urena maintains his current form.",
